
All scripts works only on a debian like systems.

"dmd_deb.sh"
============
Script to create deb packages for debian like systems.
Run it with the dmd version as argument and you'll get two deb packages (32-bit and 64-bit) in the current directory.
Resulting package should be installable on any debian like system (debian, ubuntu, linuxmint, etc.).
If "dmd.x.xxx.zip" already exist in the current folder, will be used, if not, will try to download first.
If "dmd-completion" file is in the current folder, will be included in the package.
Works with dmd 1.073/2.058 and newer.



"dmd_rpm.sh"
============
Script to create rpm packages for fedora and openSUSE.
Run it with the dmd version as argument and you'll get four rpm packages in the current directory.
Resulting package should be installable on fedora/centos and openSUSE, for 32-bit and 64-bit.
If "dmd.x.xxx.zip" already exist in the current folder, will be used, if not, will try to download first.
If "dmd-completion" file is in the current folder, will be included in the package.
Works with dmd 1.073/2.058 and newer.



"dmd_arch.sh"
============
Script to create installable packages for Arch Linux.
Run it with the dmd version as argument and you'll get two package (32-bit and 64-bit) in the current directory.
Resulting package should be installable on an Arch Linux system.
If "dmd.x.xxx.zip" already exist in the current folder, will be used, if not, will try to download first.
If "dmd-completion" file is in the current folder, will be included in the package.
Works with dmd 1.073/2.058 and newer.



"dmd_apt.sh"
============
Script to create all needed files to build a one-folder minimalist apt server for dmd.
Run it with the dmd version as argument.
Require both (32-bit and 64-bit) dmd deb files (or symbolic links to them) in the current directory and a key to sign.
Generated files: "Packages" "Packages.gz" "Release" "Release.gpg"
Works with dmd v2.058 and newer.



